1
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:25,640
♪ I have a heart and know how to love ♪

2
00:00:25,720 --> 00:00:30,200
♪ Especially when I see you
I keep seeing the scenes ♪

3
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:33,640
♪ From when we were together ♪

4
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:36,840
♪ But I keep seeing you in my head ♪

5
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:41,560
♪ My broken heart hasn't recovered ♪

6
00:00:41,640 --> 00:00:44,160
♪ So I hurt you ♪

7
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:49,480
♪ Even though I have to
Make myself watch you cry ♪

8
00:00:51,160 --> 00:00:55,760
♪ I hate it but I still do it ♪

9
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:59,720
♪ I keep picking at scabs to hurt you ♪

10
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:07,280
♪ I want to escape
But it feels like walking in circles ♪

11
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:12,000
♪ In the end I hurt myself
Keeping my love hidden ♪

12
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,240
♪ I can't walk away even if I want to ♪

13
00:01:15,240 --> 00:01:20,280
♪ My love must be hidden
I can hardly stand it ♪

14
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:23,160
♪ It's torture when you cry ♪

15
00:01:23,240 --> 00:01:27,040
♪ The more you're hurt ♪

16
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:31,160
♪ The weaker my heart becomes ♪

17
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:37,640
♪ I try not to love you
Holding back my tears while saying goodbye ♪

18
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:41,840
♪ But I could never do it for real ♪

19
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:45,600
I didn’t expect my mother
to give an interview like that.

20
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:47,760
Lada, let me ask you something.

21
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:49,640
Are you never going to love a man?

22
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:50,760
I love women,

23
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:53,040
and that woman has to be Earn only.

24
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:56,680
Are you sure
you’re ready for the pressure

25
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:59,840
-that’s going to hit you out of nowhere?
-I'm ready.

26
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:02,200
How can two women truly love each other?

27
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:04,400
They can't build a proper family.

28
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,640
I know you're hurt,

29
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:07,800
but Lada is probably just as hurt as you.

30
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:10,039
Dear!

31
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:12,760
Dear!

32
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:23,920
And Earn will be
the last most important person in my life.

33
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:43,600
Doc,

34
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,560
are you okay?

35
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,520
I'm okay.

36
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:53,080
I'm not feeling unwell or anything.

37
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:09,880
Do you know

38
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:12,720
what's the hardest thing we can hide?

39
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:17,480
Our feelings.

40
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:21,240
There's no way
we can completely hide it.

41
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:28,120
It'll show itself one way or another.

42
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:46,480
You want to reconcile
with your mother, don’t you?

43
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:55,160
I think...

44
00:03:58,360 --> 00:04:00,640
I’ve done so much for her already.

45
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,920
It's time to do things for myself.

46
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:10,360
That is enough.

47
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:19,040
If you decide to go that way,

48
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,800
I’ll always be by your side.

49
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,920
Hungry? I'll cook something for you.

50
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:37,640
Where are you going?

51
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:40,040
Well, I'm going to get something
for you to eat.

52
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:42,440
I'm not hungry,
you're not allowed to go.

53
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:45,160
Hello!

54
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:50,600
I heard that this house
has a newlywed couple.

55
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:52,120
May I join in the celebration as well?

56
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,680
We're not married yet.

57
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,720
But soon...

58
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,280
Perhaps?

59
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:04,080
It stinks of love.

60
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:07,240
Hey! I bought a lot of stuff.

61
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,720
What did you buy, Suzie?

62
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,760
We're having a hearty meal.

63
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:11,960
I'm not letting you go.

64
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:13,320
Let go.

65
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,320
You bought snacks. Won't I turn fat?

66
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,320
FATHER

67
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,520
No! Just look at me.

68
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,680
Father.

69
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,720
Hello, Father.

70
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:07,440
Your mother is experiencing
End Stage Heart Failure

71
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:11,240
and also has
Intractable Ventricular Arrhythmia.

72
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:14,160
After performing CPR for half an hour,

73
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:17,320
the vital signs kept deteriorating.

74
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:23,440
Why didn’t she ever tell me
she was sick?

75
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:26,800
She probably didn’t want you to worry.

76
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,560
You know her well.

77
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,920
Suzie.

78
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,400
Why do I feel so terrible?

79
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,400
Terrible?

80
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:09,400
About?

81
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:12,480
You didn't do anything to Doctor's mother.

82
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:14,760
But if I hadn't revealed our relationship,

83
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:18,040
if I had chosen to stay where I belong,

84
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,480
there'd have been no problem.

85
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:23,680
But because I chose to reveal it,

86
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:25,400
everything turned out this way.

87
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:29,360
No, dear.

88
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:30,760
Don't overthink it.

89
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:34,640
It's not a big deal, don't overthink it.

90
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,760
You can't stop people from being sick.

91
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,080
Right now,

92
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:41,960
your doctor needs a lot of encouragement.

93
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:45,080
You must not be unfaltering.

94
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:10,880
Doc.

95
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:17,920
Umm...

96
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:19,800
Doctor,

97
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:22,200
the director invites you to his room.

98
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:46,680
Lada, come and listen together.

99
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:58,280
Please continue, Doctor.

100
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,320
The operation was quite challenging,

101
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:05,160
but now Lady Russamee's vital signs are stable.

102
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:07,120
During the intraoperative period,
there was active bleeding,

103
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,720
leading to significant blood loss.

104
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:10,040
She hasn't regained consciousness yet,

105
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:11,960
possibly due to cerebral hypoxia

106
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,240
when her blood pressure dropped.

107
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,840
It's uncertain when she'll wake up

108
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:16,680
and whether she will fully recover.

109
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:31,000
During the post-operative period,

110
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:34,720
ensure there are no events that
could trigger stress for the patient,

111
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:38,760
it can potentially lead to arrhythmias
and unstable vital signs.

112
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:42,080
Yes, I understand.

113
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:40,480
You take such a long rest this time.

114
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:47,240
You usually only sleep
for a few hours, right?

115
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:52,480
Could it be that you're angry with me?

116
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,200
I'm sorry.

117
00:12:57,800 --> 00:12:59,960
I'm sorry for speaking badly to you.

118
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:02,680
I'm sorry for not behaving well.

119
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:05,560
I'm sorry for...

120
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:09,560
being unable to be what you desire.

121
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:17,880
I want you to give me another chance.

122
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,400
Can you please wake up?

123
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:24,640
I promise to be a good girl.

124
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,040
Please, Mother?

125
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:32,480
I love you.

126
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:43,200
Mother,

127
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:45,160
can you hear me?

128
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,400
Please inform the doctor that

129
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,400
Lady Russamee has regained consciousness.

130
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,440
Yes.

131
00:14:58,760 --> 00:15:00,000
Are you hungry?

132
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:01,840
Do you want coffee,

133
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:03,240
sandwiches or anything?

134
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,960
I'll go buy it for you.

135
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:06,240
It's alright.

136
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:08,200
I'm not hungry.

137
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:29,320
Doc.

138
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:36,120
Should we take a break for a while?

139
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,840
You promised not to get tired of my problems.

140
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:54,280
I've never grown tired of your problems.

141
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:07,640
However, you need to
spend most of your time with your mother.

142
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:10,800
Take the utmost care of her.

143
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:15,920
You only have one mother, after all.

144
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:22,720
I'm not going anywhere.

145
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:28,280
Whenever you take a glance back,

146
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,000
I'll still be inside here.

147
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:45,880
We just need to take a break

148
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:48,960
because your mother
needs you the most right now.

149
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:54,840
But this break could mean

150
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:57,880
being apart forever.

151
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,319
On the outside,

152
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:24,400
I may not exist in your life,

153
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:31,400
but inside here,

154
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:36,360
I am the owner of your heart.

155
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:48,680
You are the owner of my heart,

156
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:52,320
the first...

157
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:00,840
and...

158
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:06,800
the last.

159
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:27,080
♪ I have a heart and know how to love ♪

160
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:31,880
♪ Especially when I see you
I keep seeing the scenes ♪

161
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:34,880
♪ From when we were together ♪

162
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:38,080
♪ But I keep seeing you in my head ♪

163
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:43,000
♪ My broken heart hasn't recovered ♪

164
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:45,440
♪ So I hurt you... ♪

165
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:46,440
Mother.

166
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:49,520
♪ Even though I have to
Make myself watch you cry... ♪

167
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:50,520
Earn!

168
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:57,760
♪ I hate it but I still do it ♪

169
00:19:57,760 --> 00:20:01,720
♪ I keep picking at scabs to hurt you ♪

170
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:09,600
♪ I want to escape
But it feels like walking in circles ♪

171
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:13,760
♪ In the end I hurt myself
Keeping my love hidden ♪

172
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:17,160
♪ I can't walk away even if I want to ♪

173
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:22,200
♪ My love must be hidden
I can hardly stand it ♪

174
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:25,160
♪ It's torture when you cry ♪

175
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:29,200
♪ The more you're hurt ♪

176
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:32,880
♪ The weaker my heart becomes ♪

177
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:39,160
♪ I try not to love you
Holding back my tears while saying goodbye ♪

178
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:43,840
♪ But I could never do it for real ♪

179
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:55,280
♪ It may seem like I don't love you
That I'm okay ♪

180
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:59,960
♪ But the truth is, inside my heart
Every time I hurt you... ♪

181
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Lada.

182
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:03,360
♪ I feel heartbroken ♪

183
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:04,800
Mother.

184
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:06,840
♪ The pain is too much to describe ♪

185
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:09,360
♪ The more I see you sad... ♪

186
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:10,360
Are you thirsty?

187
00:21:10,360 --> 00:21:11,840
♪ The more I break down ♪

188
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:14,680
I will get you some water.

189
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:15,680
Thank you, dear.

190
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:19,840
♪ But it just can't be done ♪

191
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:25,880
♪ I hate it but I still do it ♪

192
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:29,840
♪ I keep picking at scabs to hurt you ♪

193
00:21:29,840 --> 00:21:37,400
♪ I want to escape
But it feels like walking in circles ♪

194
00:21:37,760 --> 00:21:42,120
♪ In the end I hurt myself
Keeping my love hidden ♪

195
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:45,320
♪ I can't walk away even if I want to ♪

196
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:50,320
♪ My love must be hidden
I can hardly stand it ♪

197
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:53,320
♪ It's torture when you cry ♪

198
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:57,320
♪ The more you're hurt ♪

199
00:21:57,320 --> 00:22:01,280
♪ The weaker my heart becomes ♪

200
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:07,240
♪ I try not to love you
Holding back my tears while saying goodbye ♪

201
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:12,120
♪ But I could never do it for real ♪

202
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:54,200
-Take it easy.
-Don't worry.

203
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:56,040
-Slowly, dear.
-I'm okay.

204
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:01,600
It's almost time for medicine.

205
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:03,920
I'll get the medicines for you.

206
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:04,960
Alright.

207
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:15,520
Where did that girl go?

208
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,120
She's gone.

209
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:22,360
Why did she suddenly...

210
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:25,240
She chose to leave...

211
00:23:26,360 --> 00:23:28,400
because she knew that if she stayed,

212
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:31,400
you and Lada would fight again.

213
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,520
So, she chose to leave.

214
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:47,680
May I ask you directly?

215
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:51,760
Is it because of me that she became ill?

216
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:53,240
Don't blame yourself,

217
00:23:53,560 --> 00:23:55,240
there's no one at fault here.

218
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:56,760
But to be honest,

219
00:23:57,320 --> 00:23:59,520
Lada's mother really needs her right now.

220
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:02,600
At this moment, Lada needs to
take utmost care of her mother.

221
00:24:08,560 --> 00:24:09,600
I understand.

222
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:15,360
I'll be the one to back out.

223
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:18,120
But...

224
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:20,760
won't that make you sad?

225
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:27,400
I'll be sad.

226
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:31,920
Extremely sad.

227
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:35,080
But being in love with each other...

228
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:38,160
is not enough,

229
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:41,640
we also need to understand each other.

230
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:44,880
I deeply understand her

231
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:47,840
and know how difficult it is for her.

232
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:51,840
However, if two people holding
each other's hands

233
00:24:51,840 --> 00:24:53,520
are causing things to fall,

234
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:58,520
and if someone has to let go,

235
00:25:00,880 --> 00:25:02,520
that person should be me.

236
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:08,720
I'm glad that...

237
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:12,160
our daughter has met someone like Earn.

238
00:25:12,960 --> 00:25:15,680
She is the kind of person
who can make our daughter happy.

239
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:17,840
But she's a woman.

240
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:18,880
So?

241
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:21,920
Since our daughter loves her

242
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:24,280
and she loves our daughter,

243
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:26,280
where is the problem?

244
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,720
Without prejudice,

245
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:33,400
you'll be able to see
how much they love each other.

246
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:38,040
Their love is stronger than we thought.

247
00:25:57,160 --> 00:25:58,320
Thank you.

248
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:09,600
♪ In the end I hurt myself
Keeping my love hidden ♪

249
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:12,760
♪ I can't walk away even if I want to ♪

250
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:15,200
♪ My love must be hidden ♪

251
00:26:17,040 --> 00:26:19,080
What more do you want from me?

252
00:26:19,560 --> 00:26:21,920
I chose to lay low, to be non-existent.

253
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:23,920
Is that still not enough for you?

254
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:26,760
What if I were to say that
it's still not enough?

255
00:26:27,280 --> 00:26:28,600
What would you say?

256
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:31,600
Lada.

257
00:27:43,560 --> 00:27:44,880
Yes, Mother?

258
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,040
Who is it?

259
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:36,920
Lady Russamee, hello.

260
00:28:43,080 --> 00:28:44,600
I'll be direct with you.

261
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:50,880
How much do you love my daughter?

262
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:56,560
Do you know that
Lada's not just a doctor,

263
00:28:57,480 --> 00:28:59,600
but she will also have to
become a director?

264
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,760
A director has to be responsible
for tens of thousands of people.

265
00:29:04,800 --> 00:29:07,120
Are you ready to handle all that pressure

266
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:10,880
and commit to taking care of each other
until you grow old?

267
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:24,560
What more do you want from me?

268
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:29,440
I have already backed out as much as I can.

269
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:37,560
I chose to lay low, to be non-existent.

270
00:29:39,800 --> 00:29:41,840
I chose to live quietly,

271
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:46,120
hidden in the narrowest corner of her heart.

272
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:50,440
I even chose to quit
the entertainment world that I love.

